item.title: What is the middle of your finger called?

In the hand, the prominent, knobby ends of the phalanges are known as knuckles. The proximal phalanges join with the metacarpals of the hand or metatarsals of the foot at the metacarpophalangeal joint or metatarsophalangeal joint.

When fishing from a pier, species-specific gear restrictions (such as for rockfish, lingcod, and salmon) do apply. Is it legal to fish in California with two rods? Anglers with a valid two-rod stamp, as well as anglers under the age of 16, may use up to two rods in inland waters where angling is permitted, with the exception of places where only artificial lures or barbless hooks are permitted.
